    "The R Hα distributions with stellar atmospheric parameters (such as the R Hα distribution with T eff shown in Figure 5) have been investigated in detail in He et al (2023).",
    "In this work, we focus on the variability of the R Hα values.",
    "It can be seen from Figure 5a that for each stellar source, the values of the multiple R Hα measurements are generally not a constant and fluctuate within a certain range.",
    "This variability of the R Hα values will be quantitatively evaluated in Section 4.2.",
    "In the literature, the variability of stellar activity for a stellar source is often indicated by the STD (standard deviation) of the multiple measurements of an activity index (e.g., Lockwood et al 2007; Hall et al 2009; Gomes da Silva et al 2021) as introduced in Section 1."
